<br>
8.4 Kill one of the centaur chief in the 4 camps in the SW corner of Green Glades. One of the Chiefs, NOT the lord. May be difficult for one group if not built right. If necessary, bring 2 groups and do it twice. Make sure the group that needs gets kill shot on second go around.<br>
<br>
8.5 Kratos – Only one person in groupneeds to get the items for Kratos, but it may be safer to have everyone get quests from him. First you need to find him to get quest from him. This is probably the most difficult part of this trial because he wanders all over the place. Once you find him, he’ll give you a grocery list of items he needs. <br>
<br>
1) Giant Ketos Fillet (automatic drop from a regular Ketos) <br>
<br>
Go by Temple of Twilight (most known place for Ketos, IMHO) and kill the ketos that spawns right above it. If you have the quest in your journal, you'll get a Giant Ketos Fillet. Nov 25<br>
ketos also seen at game time 8h 30m meso 13k, 23k swimming past the columns.<br>
<br>
2) The first named is named Ghita, and she is in northern AG in ruins with lots of oj statues outside her, who aid her in owning anyone who pulls her. She's simple enough, just pull statues then her and everyone in the group gets Ghita's stone. <br>
<br>
3) Oasis Spring Waters (the Oasis is in Stygia/Land of Atum [Can't remember which zone, sorry.] <br>
<br>
The oasis water is in Stygian Delta, somewhere. Just go to it until you get a message about soothing water and do /forage. It weighs 10 so be sure to dump it in the vault if you're weak. <br>
<br>
4) Kratos' chest is given to you if you choose correctly in Gaspara's game. If you choose incorrectly, you'll have to fight monsters. - Be warned, if a fire elemental spawns, use magic. It's weak against it. <br>
<br>
The chest is a bit trickier, there is a named Neutral jinni who is red and spawns 4-5 chests. If you choose incorrectly a very high level fire elemental spawns (level 75-80). If you choose right, someone in the party gets Kratos's Chest.<br>
<br>
5) The six heads of Creon's sons. These are near the boarder of Arbor Glen and Green Glades. They are in the village directly next to Tholo's Tournament in the flying temple. <br>
<br>
The 6 named are Sons of Creon, all named centaurs. They can be found in the village east of the lake in AG. Pull one and you get like 25 ojs-grapes who stun, mez, dot, and all that fun stuff.<br>
<br>
Once you have all the items go find Kratos and talk to him again. He’ll give you a bag, and you need to /use the bag to put all the items in it and return it to him. That should complete quest for entire group.<br>
<br>
8.7 Agne’s Torso – This one is simple. Just kill self-maintaining statues in the camp E-SE of Aerus Haven until one of them drops the Torso. That should complete quest for group.<br>
<br>
8.9 Agne’s Right Arm – This one is located at 13/10 Arbor Glen. 2 options here. Either kill all the statues and then get the Arm out of the chest and run out of the hall. Or kill half the statues then have the healers in your group heal and insta you to make sure you get out of hall with arm, some extra statues will pop when you do it this way I believe.<br>
